<item>
            <title>[LU-17393] OI Scrub does not repair LAST_ID on MDT</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17393</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Found during code review of LFSCK, it seems only to recreate the &lt;tt&gt;LAST_ID&lt;/tt&gt; file on OSTs and not recreate &lt;tt&gt;LAST_ID&lt;/tt&gt; on MDTs.  This should be checked during &quot;initial scrub&quot; when the filesystem is mounted. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;LAST_ID&lt;/tt&gt; file could also be recreated when finding the quota index file, but it will set the content of the file to be the first OID incorrectly. It should also verify and repair the LMA of the LAST_ID file. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
